What is Json?

	Json stands for javascript object notation.

	It contains only properties, objects and collections. there are no methods.

	It is a very popular type of document to transmit information between 2 programs - It's used heavily for APIs

	Json is natively supported by Javascript because it is derived from it

	Java as well as other languages have lots of libraries that allow them to work with Json files

	What does Json look like?

		Json files just look like a plain text file

			Example:

				{
					property: value
				}

				{
					user: [
						name: "John"
						age: 25
						jobTitle: "SDET"
						]
				}

	Cucumber JSON

		Cucumber is able to generate a JSON report.

			That file can be used